SIMPLE: aseptic
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Aseptic
<hw>A*sep"tic</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>a-</ets> not + <ets>septic</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not
liable to putrefaction; nonputrescent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>free from pathogenic microorganisms; sterile;
<as>as, <ex>aseptic</ex> operating conditions</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <mark>[metaphorical]</mark> <def>lacking emotion, human
warmth, or excitement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aseptic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Aseptic
<hw>A*sep"tic</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An aseptic
substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Asexual</ent>⟦br⟧
